data.meta_description: Casimir I the Restorer (Polish: Kazimierz I Odnowiciel; b. Krakow, 25 July 1016 - d. Poznan, 28 November 1058), was a Duke of Poland of the Piast dynasty and the de facto monarch of the entire country since 1034 until his death.  He was the only son of Mieszko II Lambert by his wife Richeza, daughter of Count Palatine...
